## Deliverable A — **Per-move prompt set** (user cannot list these; you always include)

For **each** requested action (e.g. `right_punch`, `left_kick`, `chord_bicycle_kick`), output **three prompts** (windup, peak, follow-through) using this **exact scaffold**:

```text
[MOVE_ID] [PHASE] — John Stick reference frame
Subject: Stylized stick figure, black silhouette-friendly, rounded ball joints at shoulders/elbows/wrists/hips/knees/ankles.
Pose: <explicit: which arm/leg extended, spine lean, head tilt, COG over which foot>
Action read: <one sentence: what a player should “read” in 0.1s>
Camera: <orthographic side | ¾ front-right | isometric 35°>, lens neutral, no dramatic FOV
Style: <e.g. flat cel shading, crisp outline 3px equivalent, no muscle anatomy>
Costume: <player default: minimal / or list modules>
Lighting: soft top-front key, subtle cool rim, no harsh ground shadow
Background: solid #<hex> OR full transparent alpha
Output: PNG <W>x<H>, <single frame | 4×4 sprite sheet, cell 256×256, 16px gutter>, centered, consistent scale
Negative prompt: photorealistic skin, facial detail, extra limbs, duplicate arms, motion blur, blood, text, watermark, logo, busy environment, depth of field bokeh
Consistency token (reuse across set): "JohnStick_ref_v1, thick limbs, round joints, cel outline, martial brawler"
```

For **chord / compound** moves, add lines:

```text
Chord note: Compound move — exaggerate extension + airborne silhouette + clear negative space; apex frame is hero marketing frame.
Hit targets: <which limb contacts first; secondary follow-through limb>
```

## Deliverable B — **Style sheet prompt** (one block)

Generate a **single** master prompt to lock DNA for all future frames:

```text
Character style bible sheet, turnaround + 6 emotionless pose silhouettes, stick fighter, modular outfit slots labeled (hat, torso, legs), orthographic front/side/back, color flats separated from line, game-ready readability, John Stick project
```

## Working with a non-expert user (ask only if blocking)

Max **3 questions:** (1) 2D vs 3D deliverable? (2) Player accent color? (3) Reference game or image link?

If silent: **proceed with defaults** and label them **DEFAULT** in the doc.

## Anti-patterns

- Prompts missing **phase** or **negative prompt** — amateur output guaranteed.
- “Cool pose” that **hides** which button the move maps to.
- Inconsistent **scale tokens** across a move family (breaks sprite sheets).
